title: Corn Chowder
ingredients: ["bacon, sliced", "1 small onion", "1/2 red pepper, diced", "1 c. potato, sliced", "2 c. milk", "1 (14 to 16 oz.) can kernel corn", "1 (14 to 16 oz.) can creamed corn"]
directions: ["Saute bacon and diced onion into large saucepan.", "Add milk, red pepper, potato and corn.", "Let cook on medium heat until it thickens.", "Let it simmer until ready to eat."]

title: Whoopee Pies
ingredients: ["2 c. flour", "1 tsp. soda", "1/4 tsp. salt", "1 egg", "3/4 c. milk", "1/3 c. oil", "1 tsp. vanilla", "1/3 c. cocoa", "1 c. sugar"]
directions: ["Sift together flour, soda and salt.", "Add egg, milk, oil, vanilla, cocoa and sugar.", "Drop by teaspoonfuls and bake at 350\u00b0 for 10 to 15 minutes."]

title: Chicken Cacciatore
ingredients: ["1 c. chopped celery", "1 medium green pepper", "1/8 c. dry onion flakes", "1 1/2 c. tomato sauce", "1 Tbsp. oregano", "1/2 tsp. basil", "1 1/2 Tbsp. parsley", "3/4 c. sliced mushrooms", "3 1/2 lb. chicken, cut up", "salt and pepper to taste"]
directions: ["Cook celery, onion and pepper in small amount of oil until tender.", "Add tomato sauce, seasonings and mushrooms.", "Pour over chicken and bake at 350\u00b0 until chicken is done, about 1 hour."]
